The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	Five Bengal paddlers have been selected to represent India in the ongoing South Asian (Junior) Table Tennis Championship in Karachi. The nine-member squad will be accompanied by coach Abhijit Das from South Eastern Railways and manager G. Ravichandran from Tamil Nadu. The finals will be held on Saturday.      
	Squads:      
	Boys: Soumyajit Ghosh, Raj Mondal and Sourav Saha (Bengal); G Satyen (Tamil Nadu); Subham Sharma (Andhra Pradesh). Girls: Ankita Das and Soumi Mondal (Bengal); Nikita Banu (Karnataka), Charvi Kawle (Maharashtra).                
	Football: Arun Ghosh exhibition match between IFA XI and East Bengal at Barasat Stadium from 5 pm.                                                                                                                                                                     
